1. FizzBuzz rules and precise algorithm
- For each integer n in sequence starting at 1 (or configurable start):
  - If n % 3 === 0 and n % 5 === 0 => output the exact string: fizzbuzz
  - Else if n % 3 === 0 => output the exact string: fizz
  - Else if n % 5 === 0 => output the exact string: buzz
  - Else => output the decimal representation of n
- Variations to be considered and implemented explicitly when required: digit-contains rule (treat numbers containing the digit 3 as divisible-by-3 rule, etc.), additional divisors (e.g., 7), and configurable mapping of divisor->token.
- Deterministic sequence example (first 20): 1,2,fizz,4,buzz,fizz,7,8,fizz,buzz,11,fizz,13,14,fizzbuzz,16,17,fizz,19,buzz

