  - Use node --input-type=module when evaluating code snippets
- Module specifier types and precise rules:
  - Relative specifiers: './file.js' or '../path/file.mjs' — file extension mandatory for relative/absolute specifiers
  - Bare specifiers: 'package' or 'package/subpath' — resolved via package exports or package main resolution; file extension required only if package has no "exports" mapping
  - Absolute specifiers: full file: or node: URLs; file: and node: supported
- Mandatory behavior to implement in loaders/import resolution:
